---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Resume — Jonathan Jackson" description="15+ years building web infrastructure, observability platforms, and developer tooling at scale." ogImage="/og/resume.png">
  <div class="resume">

    <header class="resume-header">
      <h1>Jonathan Jackson</h1>
      <p class="contact">
        <a href="mailto:me@jonathanjackson.dev">me@jonathanjackson.dev</a>
        <span>·</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/rondale-sc">github.com/rondale-sc</a>
        <span>·</span>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jonathanpjackson">linkedin.com/in/jonathanpjackson</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <p>15+ years building web infrastructure, observability platforms, and developer tooling at scale. At LinkedIn, shipped the OpenTelemetry instrumentation that runs in production across LinkedIn.com today, drove the modernization of legacy observability systems (spanning site performance tracking and dashboarding solutions, some over 15 years old) through a combination of pipeline modernization and full platform migration, and piloted the initial evaluation framework for LinkedIn's AI-powered alert-triage platform. Comfortable moving across the full stack (TypeScript/Ember/React client, Go Grafana plugins, backend services, Kafka consumers, and agentic tooling) and at driving multi-team migration programs from inception through production.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2>Experience</h2>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div class="entry-title-block">
            <span class="entry-company">LinkedIn</span>
            <span class="entry-role">Staff Software Engineer</span>
          </div>
          <span class="entry-date">May 2022 – Present</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Drove LinkedIn's web client OpenTelemetry SDK from zero to 100% production traffic. Built core SDK primitives, a runtime span-validation framework that catches schema violations before they reach production, and full instrumentation coverage for INP web vitals, page load time, and exception telemetry. This instrumentation runs in every page load on LinkedIn.com today.</li>
          <li>Built a Grafana datasource plugin and migrated ~5,000 production dashboards off a third-party solution to the in-house alternative, improving support for those use cases without disrupting the teams depending on them.</li>
          <li>Contributed to early-stage evaluation work for Observe Agent, LinkedIn's AI-powered alert-triage platform, including P0 incident dataset curation and initial LLM evaluation methodology.</li>
          <li>Improved the curated user experience and supporting infrastructure of LinkedIn's Observability platform, delivering a more capable and polished alert-triage experience for on-call engineers.</li>
          <li>Drove a targeted effort to modernize and harden the test infrastructure for LinkedIn's Observability tooling, migrating to Playwright and running a sustained reliability program to ensure stability as AI-assisted development accelerated the team's delivery pace.</li>
          <li>Built conversion tooling for a large-scale, ongoing migration of 80,000+ production dashboards from a legacy metric system to its modern MDM-based equivalent (some dashboards over a decade old and still actively used), focusing on the read path and producing metric-level equivalence between old and new systems.</li>
          <li>Drove the end-of-life of a 15-year-old site performance monitoring tool, establishing feature parity in its modern replacement and orchestrating the transition so dependent teams experienced no operational disruption.

Maintained LinkedIn's open-source web benchmarking tool, <a href="https://tracerbench.com">TracerBench</a>, as part of a shift-left performance initiative, delivering robust benchmarking across multiple LinkedIn web products at scale, leveraging deep Ember.js expertise to instrument and validate performance at the framework level.</li>
          <li>Worked to define and establish performance and availability metrics across LinkedIn's Observability tooling, creating clearer visibility into the health of the platform itself.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div class="entry-title-block">
            <span class="entry-company">Addepar</span>
            <span class="entry-role">Software Engineer</span>
          </div>
          <span class="entry-date">Feb 2019 – Apr 2022</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Built and maintained Addepar's report editor, the primary tool financial advisors use to generate client-facing portfolio reports from Addepar's financial graph (a platform tracking $1T+ in assets across thousands of advisory firms). Delivered reporting features that translated complex multi-asset portfolio data into structured, client-ready outputs.</li>
          <li>Extended the report editor's query and rendering capabilities to handle increasingly complex financial instruments and custom firm configurations, working closely with the platform team on the underlying graph API.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <h3>Selected Earlier Experience</h3>
        <ul class="earlier">
          <li><strong>201 Created, Senior Developer</strong> (Jan 2017 – Feb 2019): Senior developer at one of the first consultancies to adopt Ember.js. Built client applications across fintech, media, and e-commerce, with deep focus on Ember component architecture and front-end performance.</li>
          <li><strong>Hashrocket, Senior Developer</strong> (May 2013 – Dec 2016): Senior developer and consultant at a leading Rails consultancy. Architected applications and trained junior developers across clients in healthcare, banking, fashion, hospitality, and sports. Co-hosted Ember Weekend podcast; delivered Ember.js training to 40+ developers at Modern Web.</li>
          <li><strong>Pro Medical, Inc., Software Engineer</strong> (2009 – 2013): First engineering role after graduation. Built internal web tooling and managed IT for a HIPAA-compliant medical billing company.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div class="entry-title-block">
            <span class="entry-company">University of Florida</span>
            <span class="entry-role">BA, Political Science</span>
          </div>
          <span class="entry-date">2008</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      <div class="skills">
        <div class="skill-group">
          <span class="skill-label">Languages</span>
          <span>TypeScript, JavaScript, Go, Ruby</span>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <span class="skill-label">Frameworks</span>
          <span>Ember.js, React, Rails, Elixir/Phoenix</span>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <span class="skill-label">Infrastructure</span>
          <span>OpenTelemetry, Grafana, Kafka, Playwright, Cypress</span>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-group">
          <span class="skill-label">Domains</span>
          <span>Observability, Web Performance, AI/LLM Evaluation, Developer Tooling</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="resume-section">
      <h2>Speaking &amp; Community</h2>
      <ul class="speaking">
        <li><strong>RailsConf 2015</strong>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NnquHUlh0Pk">"Rails and EmberCLI: an integration love story"</a></li>
        <li><strong>EmberFest EU 2018</strong>, speaker</li>
        <li><strong>Ember NYC</strong>, speaker</li>
        <li><strong>EmberJAX</strong>, founder and multi-year organizer of the Jacksonville, FL Ember.js meetup</li>
        <li><strong>Ember Weekend</strong>, co-host of a long-running podcast covering Ember.js news, interviews, and community</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .resume {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .resume-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .resume-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .contact {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .contact span { color: var(--border); }
  .contact a { color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .contact a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .resume-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .resume-section h2 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .resume-section > p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .entry {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .entry-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .entry-title-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .entry-company {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .entry-role {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .entry-date {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .entry h3 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .entry ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  .entry ul li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .entry ul.earlier li {
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .skills {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .skill-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .skill-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    width: 110px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .speaking {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.45rem;
  }

  .speaking li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media print {
    .resume { max-width: 100%; }
    .resume-header { border-bottom-color: #000; }
    .resume-section h2 { color: #000; border-bottom-color: #ccc; }
    .contact a { color: #444; }
  }
</style>
